Consider the following C function:

int f(int n) {
    static int r = 0;
    if (n <= 0) return 1;
    if (n > 3) {
        r = n;
        return f(n-2) + 2;
    }
    return f(n-1) + r;
}

What is the value of f(5)?

A. 3
B. 7
C. 9
D. 18

Consider the following function:

double f(double x) {
    if (abs(x*x - 3) < 0.01)
        return x;
    else
        return f(x/2 + 1.5/x);
}

Give a value q (to 2 decimals) such that f(q) will return 3: _____.

Consider the following function written in the C programming language:

void foo(char *a) {
    if (*a && *a != ' ') {
        foo(a+1);
        putchar(*a);
    }
}

The output of the above function on input "ABCD EFGH" is:

A. ABCD EFGH
B. ABCD
C. HGFE DCBA
D. DCBA
